The board shall consist of seven (7) members appointed by the Governor.
One (1) member shall be an attorney from the Office of the Attorney General to be designated by the Attorney General;
One (1) member shall be a municipal police officer of the rank of captain or above;
One (1) member shall be a county sheriff;
Three (3) members shall each have been private investigators for at least five (5) years prior to the date of their appointment and shall be of recognized business standing; and
One (1) member shall be a citizen at large who is not associated with or financially interested in the practice of private investigating.

The original members of the board shall be appointed by no later than January 1, 2003, as follows:
One (1) member to a one (1) year term;
Two (2) members to a two (2) year term;
Two (2) members to a three (3) year term; and
Two (2) members to a four (4) year term.
